## Key Conventions
- Player physics in `FixedUpdate`, input reading in `Update`
- Cache `Rigidbody2D`, `BoxCollider2D`, `Animator` in `Awake`
- Use `Physics2D.OverlapCircle` for ground/wall detection (non-alloc)
- Pool all frequently spawned objects (enemies, projectiles, particles, collectibles)
- Tilemap for level geometry, Prefabs for interactive objects
- `[SerializeField]` with `[Header]` for all tweakable parameters

## Input Map
```
Player:
  Move — Virtual Joystick (left side of screen)
  Jump — Virtual Button (right side, bottom)
  Dash — Virtual Button (right side, upper)
  Attack — Virtual Button (right side, middle)
  Interact — Tap on interactable object
```

## Physics Layers
```
0: Default
6: Player
7: Ground
8: Enemy
9: Projectile
10: Collectible
11: OneWayPlatform
```

